# Status Color System

A standardized 8-family color system for representing business entity states
across the entire application. Every status in every service maps to exactly
one family.

---

## Template Variables

- `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` -- Name of the project using this system
- `{{STATUS_MAPPING_TABLE}}` -- Project-specific status-to-family mapping (see Section 3)

---

## 1. The 8 Status Families

Each family provides 4 CSS custom properties:

| Token suffix | Purpose          | Example use                     |
|--------------|------------------|---------------------------------|
| `-bg`        | Background fill  | Badge background, row highlight |
| `-text`      | Text / icon      | Label text, icon fill           |
| `-border`    | Border stroke    | Badge border, card outline      |
| `-dot`       | Indicator dot    | DotLabel circle, timeline node  |

### Family Definitions

| Family        | CSS prefix              | Hue     | Semantic meaning                          |
|---------------|-------------------------|---------|-------------------------------------------|
| **success**   | `--status-success-*`    | Green   | Completed, active, paid, delivered, approved |
| **warning**   | `--status-warning-*`    | Amber   | Expiring, needs attention, pending review |
| **danger**    | `--status-danger-*`     | Red     | Overdue, rejected, failed, critical, cancelled |
| **info**      | `--status-info-*`       | Blue    | Informational, new, updated, notification |
| **neutral**   | `--status-neutral-*`    | Gray    | Draft, inactive, archived, unknown        |
| **in-progress** | `--status-in-progress-*` | Indigo | In transit, processing, building, loading |
| **queued**    | `--status-queued-*`     | Purple  | Scheduled, pending, waiting, on hold      |
| **special**   | `--status-special-*`    | Teal    | VIP, priority, featured, premium          |

