## 5. Accessibility Requirements

- **Contrast ratios:** All `-text` colors on their `-bg` must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for
  normal text, 3:1 for large text).
- **Not color-alone:** Status must also be conveyed via text label (the DotLabel always
  includes a text label alongside the dot).
- **Dark mode:** All families have dark-mode variants defined in `semantic-tokens.css`
  that maintain the same contrast ratios.

---

## 6. Extending the System

To add a new status family:

1. Add 4 CSS custom properties in `semantic-tokens.css` (both `:root` and `.dark`):
   ```css
   --status-{family}-bg: ...;
   --status-{family}-text: ...;
   --status-{family}-border: ...;
   --status-{family}-dot: ...;
   ```
2. Add the family to the `StatusFamily` type union.
3. Add business status mappings to `STATUS_FAMILY_MAP`.
4. The DotLabel component works automatically (it uses the family name in `var()`).
